Cancellable
public class ArtisanBlockPlaceEvent extends BlockPlaceEvent
Event is called when a player places a custom block.

Extends BlockPlaceEvent and includes the placed custom block instance. Can be used to cancel the placement or modify the block state after placement.

    • ArtisanBlockPlaceEvent

      public ArtisanBlockPlaceEvent(@NotNull @NotNull Block placedBlock, @NotNull @NotNull BlockState replacedBlockState, @NotNull @NotNull Block placedAgainst, @NotNull @NotNull ItemStack itemInHand, @NotNull @NotNull Player thePlayer, boolean canBuild, @NotNull @NotNull EquipmentSlot hand, @NotNull @NotNull ArtisanBaseBlock artisanBaseBlock, @NotNull @NotNull ArtisanBlockData placedArtisanBlockData)
      Constructs a custom block place event
      参数:
      placedBlock - the placed block instance (non-null)
      replacedBlockState - the original block state being replaced (non-null)
      placedAgainst - the adjacent block that the new block is placed against (non-null)
      itemInHand - the item in the player's hand (non-null)
      thePlayer - the player placing the block (non-null)
      canBuild - whether the player has build permission
      hand - the equipment slot used (non-null)
      artisanBaseBlock - the associated custom block definition (non-null)
      placedArtisanBlockData - the custom BlockData that will be stored (non-null)
